tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Additional Qualifying Tournament Finisher or Finished 76-100 on 2014 Web.com Tour Money List
tourBios.carHigh: 2014: Played in 12 PGA Tour Latinoamerica events and recorded three top-10s. Best performance was a T6 at the Transamerican Power Products CRV Mazatlan Open. Finished No. 30 on the Order of Merit. Competed in three tournaments on PGA Tour Canada and made one cut at the Forces and Families Open (T46)...Finished T142 at Web.com Tour Q-School.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Runner-up at the 2004 U.S. Junior Amateur... AJGA Rolex Junior All-American and runner-up at the 2005 Western Junior. Was also 2005 Junior Boys' Carolinas Player of the Year...Earned 2009 first-team All-Pac-12 honors and was a 2010 second-team All-Pac-12 selection...Named 2010 Men's Carolinas Player of the Year...Won the 2009 North and South Championship...Finished runner-up at the 2010 U.S. Junior Amateur and won the 2010 Porter Cup and Western Amateur...As 2010 U.S. Amateur runner-up, played in the 2011 Masters and U.S. Open, missing the cut in both majors.
tourBios.personal: Picked golf over other sports because he enjoyed playing with his family...Favorite course he has played is Augusta National and would one day like to play Pebble Beach...Biggest thrill in golf was finishing runner-up in the 2004 U.S. Junior Amateur...Favorite college team is the North Carolina Tarheels.
